Part 2 - Short Answer
1. The difference between an absolute path and a relative path is how the path is written. An absolute path displays the full path from root directory, while a relative path is only relative to the cwd.
2. Environment variables store configuration values used by the operating system and programs. Ex). - PATH variable is where commands are located, HOME variable is the user's home directory, and SHELL is the default shell. 
3. The role of the PATH variable when typing a command like python or git is to allow the shell to reach through the directories listed in PATH to find the executable.
4. It is helpful to run programs from the command line instead of double-clicking them because some programs may not be able to run by just double-clicking. Also the command line lets you: pass arguments, automate tasks, run scripts, and debug errors

